{
  "stem": "1581.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We would have probably dropped and died right there and then because of hunger and exposure, but by coincidence, a friend of ours, Mr.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Kurt Meyer, who was a piano-- a pianist, saw us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he, being a piano player, was in the high elite.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He entertained the SS and the German soldiers with his piano playing, and therefore, he had access to as much food as he wanted, and he brought two baskets full of bread and-- and saved our lives right there and then.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Like everything else, our life in-- in Auschwitz consisted of moping around.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were not working yet, and of course, every two or three hours there was a whistle and assembly, and we were counted, and counted again, and recounted.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And while we were standing there, we got acquainted with a new wonderful thing called selection.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The selection took place by some kind of an SS officer who went with his entourage and picked out people out of our line up who seemed to not fit enough to do labor, or elderly, and send them to the other side.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you know what happened to them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time, there was the suspicion.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But of course, we did-- we somehow couldn't believe that this is the case.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We did believe that they did away with the hopelessly sick people, crippled people, and very old people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They-- I-- we were quite sure, were eliminated one way or the other.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't know about the technicality at that time yet.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we somehow held on to the hope that our-- our people will be still alive, our families.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was one appel, or assembly, after the other, one selection after the other, the miserable nights, the freezing.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
